# Netlify redirects. Served from static/, so Hugo copies this to the site root.

# /four-hours-v2/ was a near-duplicate rewrite of /four-hours/ (79% shared
# wording, both in the sitemap, each canonicalising to itself). Google was being
# shown two competing pages for the same queries. /four-hours/ won.
#
# This rule only fires because content/four-hours-v2.html is now `draft = true`
# and is therefore no longer generated — on Netlify an existing file always beats
# a redirect rule.
/four-hours-v2/    /four-hours/    301
